{{wikipedia}}

==English==

===Etymology===
from [[Greek]] [[άγιος]] (''hagios'', '[[holy]]') + [[-γραφία]] (''-graphy'', '[[writing]]').

===Pronunciation===
(US) {{IPA|/ˌheɪdʒiˈɑgrəfi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-y|hagiograph|y}}

# a [[biography]] of a [[saint]].
# a [[biography]] which expresses [[reverence]] and [[respect]] for its subject.
#(''by extension'') a [[tactic]] [[adopted]] in [[Stalinist]] [[Russia]] to increase the [[popularity]] and [[power]] of [[Lenin]].

